<div class="content">
  <h1>What can you do</h1>
  <p>Make API requests from an interactive frontend build using Express, Node JS, React and Mongo DB.</p>
  <h2>How to make a request</h2>
  <p>Click on the GET button to make a get request from a Mongo Database. All documents in  the database are shown in a format of a card built using Bootstrap and Bulma CSS.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The green button on the right shows the date and time when POST request was made.</li>
    <li>The green button on the left is the post ID generated automatically by Mongo DB.</li>
    <li>The UPDATE button is used to send an update request to the database.</li>
    <li>The DELETE button deletes the document from the database.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Technologies involved</h3>
